8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1289, L.D. 1928, “An Act to Prohibit
10 Lodging Establishments from Providing Single-use Plastic Containers”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 15-B in §1581 by striking out all of subsections 3, 4
12 and 5 (page 2, lines 3 to 17 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 '3. Exemption. This section does not apply to a lodging establishment consisting of
14 one or more stand-alone cabins, cottages or apartments that contain 12 or fewer lodging
15 units in total, that are located on a single lot or parcel of land and that are owned by the
16 same person.
17 4. Enforcement; rules. The department shall enforce this section and may adopt rules
18 to implement this section. Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical
19 rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, amends the bill to
2244 clarify the exemptions from and the Department of Environmental Protection's
2255 enforcement authority regarding the bill's prohibition on lodging establishments providing
2266 personal health or beauty products in small plastic containers.
